## Phase 3 — Deploy the Lambda Gateway

**Goal:** Package and deploy the Python service to Lambda.

### Step 12 — Package the Lambda zip

> **Critical:** Lambda runs on `linux/arm64`. If you `pip install` on macOS, compiled C extensions
> (e.g. `numpy`, `cryptography`) will be built for the wrong architecture and will segfault or
> fail to import at runtime. Always use Docker with the Lambda base image to build the zip.

```bash
# From the repo root
cd ai-platform
mkdir -p dist/package

# Build inside the actual Lambda runtime image (linux/arm64)
docker run --rm --platform linux/arm64 \
  -v "$(pwd)":/src \
  --entrypoint /bin/bash \
  public.ecr.aws/lambda/python:3.12-arm64 \
  -c "pip install -r /src/requirements.txt -t /src/dist/package --quiet \
      && cp -r /src/ai_platform /src/dist/package/"

cd dist/package && zip -r ../ai-platform.zip . -q
echo "Zip size: $(du -sh ../ai-platform.zip | cut -f1)"
```

> **If you see `exec format error` when Docker runs:** Your machine's Docker is x86 only.
> Install QEMU: `docker run --privileged --rm tonistiigi/binfmt --install arm64`

### Step 13 — Deploy Lambda + API Gateway

```bash
cd ../../terraform
terraform apply -target=module.lambda_router -target=module.api_gateway
```

### Step 14 — Fix the Secrets Manager VPC endpoint (critical — do this before testing)

Lambda is in a private VPC. It calls Secrets Manager via an **interface VPC endpoint**.
Interface endpoints are ENIs — they need an **inbound HTTPS rule** in their security group.
Without it, the Lambda cold start hangs silently for 60 seconds then times out.

The fix is already in `terraform/modules/networking/main.tf`:

```hcl
# Lambda SG — ingress on port 443 from within the VPC
ingress {
  from_port   = 443
  to_port     = 443
  protocol    = "tcp"
  cidr_blocks = ["10.0.0.0/16"]
  description = "HTTPS from VPC for Secrets Manager interface endpoint"
}
```

If you deployed networking before this fix was in Terraform, apply it:

```bash
terraform apply -target=module.networking
```

> **Why Gateway endpoints don't need this:** Gateway endpoints (used for S3/DynamoDB) are
> route-table entries, not ENIs. Interface endpoints are different — they appear as private IPs
> inside your VPC and behave like any other network destination.

