## Phase 8 — CI/CD Pipeline

**Goal:** Never deploy manually again.

### Step 26 — Deploy the OIDC trust (Terraform)

The IAM OIDC provider and the GitHub Actions deploy role are managed by the `ci_cd` Terraform module.
The role is scoped to `repo:YOUR_ORG/YOUR_REPO:ref:refs/heads/main` — it can only be assumed from
a workflow run on the `main` branch, nowhere else.

```bash
cd terraform
terraform apply -target=module.ci_cd
# Note the output:
terraform output github_actions_role_arn
```

### Step 27 — Set the role ARN as a GitHub secret

> **Do NOT** paste the ARN directly into the workflow file — it contains your AWS account ID.
> Store it as a secret, then reference it with `${{ secrets.AWS_DEPLOY_ROLE_ARN }}`.

```bash
# Use stdin to avoid shell escaping issues with special characters
echo -n "arn:aws:iam::YOUR_ACCOUNT_ID:role/ai-platform-github-actions" \
  | gh secret set AWS_DEPLOY_ROLE_ARN
```

> **If the secret resolves to empty in the workflow:** The `gh secret set` command sometimes
> fails silently if you pass the value as a positional arg with quotes. Always pipe via stdin
> as shown above.

### Step 28 — The actual working workflow

The workflow at `.github/workflows/deploy.yml` has two separate jobs:
- `test` — runs on every push and every PR (catches issues before merge)
- `deploy` — runs only on pushes to `main`, after `test` passes

Key differences from naive implementations:
- Uses QEMU (`docker/setup-qemu-action@v3`) to run `linux/arm64` Docker on x86 runners
- Builds the zip inside `public.ecr.aws/lambda/python:3.12-arm64` — same environment as production
- Deploys both gateway and health-checker Lambda functions
- Runs a smoke test against the live `/health` endpoint post-deploy

```yaml
name: Test & Deploy

on:
  push:
    branches: [main]
  pull_request:
    branches: [main]

permissions:
  id-token: write   # required for OIDC token
  contents: read

jobs:
  test:
    name: Unit Tests
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - uses: actions/setup-python@v5
        with:
          python-version: "3.12"
          cache: pip
          cache-dependency-path: ai-platform/requirements.txt
      - name: Install dependencies
        run: pip install -r ai-platform/requirements.txt pytest pytest-asyncio
      - name: Run tests
        run: |
          cd ai-platform
          python -m pytest tests/ -v --tb=short

  deploy:
    name: Deploy to Production
    needs: test
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    if: github.ref == 'refs/heads/main' && github.event_name == 'push'
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4
      - name: Configure AWS credentials (OIDC)
        uses: aws-actions/configure-aws-credentials@v4
        with:
          role-to-assume: ${{ secrets.AWS_DEPLOY_ROLE_ARN }}
          aws-region: us-east-1
      - name: Set up QEMU (required to run arm64 containers on x86 runners)
        uses: docker/setup-qemu-action@v3
        with:
          platforms: arm64
      - name: Set up Docker Buildx
        uses: docker/setup-buildx-action@v3
      - name: Build Lambda zip (linux/arm64)
        run: |
          cd ai-platform
          mkdir -p dist/package
          docker run --rm --platform linux/arm64 \
            -v "$(pwd)":/src \
            --entrypoint /bin/bash \
            public.ecr.aws/lambda/python:3.12-arm64 \
            -c "pip install -r /src/requirements.txt -t /src/dist/package --quiet \
                && cp -r /src/ai_platform /src/dist/package/"
          cd dist/package && zip -r ../ai-platform.zip . -q
      - name: Deploy gateway Lambda
        run: |
          aws lambda update-function-code \
            --function-name ai-platform-gateway-production \
            --zip-file fileb://ai-platform/dist/ai-platform.zip \
            --architectures arm64 --region us-east-1
          aws lambda wait function-updated \
            --function-name ai-platform-gateway-production --region us-east-1
      - name: Deploy health-checker Lambda
        run: |
          aws lambda update-function-code \
            --function-name ai-platform-health-checker-production \
            --zip-file fileb://ai-platform/dist/ai-platform.zip \
            --architectures arm64 --region us-east-1
          aws lambda wait function-updated \
            --function-name ai-platform-health-checker-production --region us-east-1
      - name: Smoke test
        run: |
          API_URL="https://mt1bshinj9.execute-api.us-east-1.amazonaws.com"
          STATUS=$(curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" "$API_URL/health")
          [ "$STATUS" = "200" ] || (echo "Smoke test failed: $STATUS" && exit 1)
```

**Checkpoint:** Push to main = tests run, zip built for arm64, both Lambdas deployed, smoke test confirms the endpoint is live. ✓

